comment: Ca. 80 mL fresh ink at start. No layer overrides except for layer 0: 15 s exposure. No pause. Both prints with defects i.e. with varying height/slight tilt. Suction forces/movement of FEP film during printing caused distortion. Moreover, one print with small ripped off part at one long side (towards walls of reservoir). Both prints washed in warm tap water on printhead and then detached with a Spachtel. Put into bath with warm tap water and 15 min post-cured at RT in FormCure.
next steps: Do not print two models at once, but one.
